      "writtenOn": "2026-04-22T19:20:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is this a general problem with all models using entity-manager or isolated to this particular model?",
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "11e19a1b_6635ade5",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001381
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-23T19:42:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I believe it is general. Entity-manager never registers OperationalStatus on fan inventory objects. Any board whose fan inventory comes from entity-manager would hit this.",
      "parentUuid": "abff9e46_9c6e23a6",
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c4d7c578_f0057daf",
        "filename": "redfish-core/lib/fan.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 209,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000020
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-22T00:08:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So this doesn\u0027t work because the path is like \n/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis/fan0 ?\n\nAnd the service is entity manager?  So we instead want to look at the sensor (not inventory) for the health of the sensor?",
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f82a9684_5e4ed3be",
        "filename": "redfish-core/lib/fan.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 209,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001381
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-23T19:42:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, exactly. The fan inventory object is owned by entity-manager, which registers xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.Fan on it but not xyz.openbmc_project.State.Decorator.OperationalStatus. Functional for a fan is owned by dbus-sensors FanSensor on the tach sensor object at /xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/fan_tach/\u003cname\u003e, where the read state machine flips Functional to false after the configured number of consecutive read failures (default 5). On EBADR we fall over to that source of truth.",
      "parentUuid": "c4d7c578_f0057daf",
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a1798f07_c078e583",
        "filename": "redfish-core/lib/fan.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 210,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001621
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-22T19:20:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The PDI for this property indicates if this property is implemented it will indicate the state of the resource.[1] I did not find any documentation indicating the property could be implemented by a different object that should be checked instead. Is this documented somewhere?\n\n[1] https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/a12cc29365efc814fab77677d101f5cfa51d892b/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/State/Decorator/OperationalStatus.interface.yaml#L2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 210,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 210,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "13a89d42_ec80fa8e",
        "filename": "redfish-core/lib/fan.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 210,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001381
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-23T19:42:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027re right that the OperationalStatus PDI itself doesn\u0027t describe reading the property from a different object. The piece I\u0027m leaning on is sensor-architecture.md \"Association Type #2\", which says the inventory→sensors association lets a consumer get the low-level hardware item\u0027s Functional state from its sensors. That\u0027s the path the fallback would walk. I can make that explicit in the commit message.\n\n[1] https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/architecture/sensor-architecture.md#association-type-2-linking-a-low-level-hardware-item-to-its-sensors",
      "parentUuid": "a1798f07_c078e583",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 210,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 210,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3611116f_d646ee10",
        "filename": "redfish-core/lib/fan.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 225,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001621
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-22T19:20:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is the correct implementation here for entity-manager to expose the OperationalStatus interface for the fanPath object instead?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 224,
        "startChar": 39,
        "endLine": 225,
        "endChar": 66
      },
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "29384d8c_a6a51772",
        "filename": "redfish-core/lib/fan.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 225,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001381
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-23T19:42:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think both are probably useful: bmcweb walking the association keeps it working for any platform where the tach is the real source of truth, and entity-manager mirroring Functional onto the fan inventory helps consumers other than bmcweb.",
      "parentUuid": "3611116f_d646ee10",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 224,
        "startChar": 39,
        "endLine": 225,
        "endChar": 66
      },
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "958fb49f_501f5f86",
        "filename": "redfish-core/lib/fan.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 230,
