    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b05b86e0_de452983",
        "filename": "redfish-core/lib/fan.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 238,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001621
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-22T19:20:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Our model with multiple rotors the underlying sensors have names derived from the inventory name. They are not an exact match.\n\nThere is an association documented to connect from low level hardware item to its sensors.[1]  The utility function getFanSensorObjects[2] uses that association to return the sensors to a callback function.\n\nIf the entity-manager produced object cannot expose this interface then this association should be used instead to find the sensor reporting the status to give a supported way of finding the sensors. But my first choice would be for the fanPath object itself to expose the interface.\n\n[1] https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/92b89c6ac71f8b94f67f508102704a1cf38e68cb/architecture/sensor-architecture.md#association-type-2-linking-a-low-level-hardware-item-to-its-sensors\n[2] https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/bff66f9b658822be3fec688d56efbcef572922c5/redfish-core/include/utils/fan_utils.hpp#L71",
      "parentUuid": "353f4ae5_b831c02f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 238,
        "startChar": 63,
        "endLine": 238,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "e669a12ae1c27719893d3c99f6bfc96e01c85dde",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
